Elaphrus torreyensis Tanner, 1942: 137. Type locality: "Torrey, Wayne County, Utah" (original citation). Holotype (♀) in BYUC (Shawn M. Clark pers. comm. 2007). Synonymy established by Lindroth (1961a: 112). Note. Tanner (1942: 138) listed the type locality as "Torrey, Wayne County, Utah" but mistakenly wrote a few lines below that the holotype and a paratype [of
Elaphrus torreyensis
] were "taken at Escalante, Garfield Co[unty]."
